==English==

{{rank|might|being|day|115|through|himself|go|how}}

===Etymology===
* Middle English ''thurh, thruh, through'',
* Old English ''thurh'', 
* Old High German ''durh'' through; akin to:
* German ''durch'' through,
* Latin ''trans'' across, beyond, 
* Sanskrit ''tarati'' he crosses over.

====Preposition====
'''through'''
# From one side of an opening to the other.
#: ''I went '''through''' the window.''
# Entering, then later exiting.
#: ''I drove '''through''' the town at top speed without looking left or right.''
# Surrounded by while moving.
#: ''We slogged '''through''' the mud for hours before turning back and giving up.''
# by means of
#: ''This team believes in winning '''through''' intimidation.''

